Parameters

Example 1 : Create a String Parameter with the 3 different Category Names (Furniture, Office Supplies, Technology). Create a calculated field with Logical If Statement.
            Show the next level of detail in a hierarchy for just a selected attribute.
            
Example 2 : Give the user the option to select which Dimension to be used in the view (represent data at selected dimension level)
            by creating a Parameter with the list of all the desired “Dimensions”.
            
Example 3 : Create a chart to display the Top N and Bottom N profitable Customers of Superstore in a single view.

Example 4 : Create a Parameter to retrieve a ‘Selection’s Average Sales’ value. Display the average on the worksheet title using Parameter Action.

Example 5 : Display the Selection’s Average Sales using a Reference Line.

            

This Repository contains following files :
1. Summary of the Repository
2. Parameters-Example 1.twbx
3. Parameters-Example 2.twbx
4. Parameters-Example 3.twbx
5. Parameters-Example 4.twbx
6. Parameters-Example 5.twbx
7. Data Source : Sample Superstore.xls
